#: ../../udapp.md:28
msgid "The functions' buttons can have different colors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../udapp.md:30
msgid "Blue buttons are for `view` or `pure` functions. Clicking a blue button does not create a new transaction - so there will be **no gas fees**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../udapp.md:32
msgid "Orange buttons are for `non-payable` functions. Non-payable functions change the state of the contract BUT **do not accept value** (typically ETH) being sent with the transaction. Clicking an orange button will create a transaction and will cost gas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../udapp.md:34
msgid "Red buttons are for `payable` functions. Clicking a red button will create a new transaction and this transaction can accept a **value** (typically ETH). The amount of value is set in the **Value** field which is under the Gas Limit field."
msgstr ""

